comment.author: 99294911@N00
comment._content: Are you sure this isn't Custom House in Dublin? I've been staring at it a long time and I really don't think it's Greenwich! This must've been taken from the opposite bank, and that's too near to be the Isle of Dogs. Here's a picture from Dublin: secure.flickr.com/photos/jptournut/3617627790/ You can make out urns on the cornice in this photo, which Greenwich doesn't have, and a statue on top of the dome. (I've never even been to Dublin! I was just looking to see if Custom House in London had a dome, and the one in Dublin popped up in the search....)

comment.author: 11334970@N05
comment._content:
[http://www.flickr.com/photos/helga-woo] 
Hi Helga
Thanks for questioning this! A curator has taken a detailed look at this image and agrees that it is of Dublin's Custom House. The architecture of the building has a resemblance to the buildings in Greenwich which resulted in an incorrect identification as to the location.

Many thanks for your help.

Lucinda
